com.camerontec.catalys.util.marketdata

Class StandardMarketDataStore

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.util.marketdata.StandardMarketDataStore
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IMarketDataStore

    public class StandardMarketDataStore
extends Object
implements IMarketDataStore
    Standard implementation of IMarketDataStore.

    Market data services - ie objects that process a source of market data will typically create an instance of this object to store the market data. That instance will be exposed using their getMarketDataStore method.

    Access to instrumentsByBytes and instrumentsByString are synchronised using instrumentsByString object.

      • addInstrumentDepthListener

        public void addInstrumentDepthListener(IInstrument instrument,
                                       IInstrumentDepthListener listener,
                                       String requestID)
                                throws SubscriptionException
        Description copied from interface: IMarketDataStore
        Register a listener to depth (aggregated) updates on the given instrument.

        If this listener is already registered, does nothing (in other words implementations must check for duplicate listeners).

        Errors

        This request to listen (ie subscribe) can fail immediately, in which case a SubscriptionException is thrown. However, it may also fail later, after the method has returned. This can happen if a corresponding subscription request needs to be sent back to a remote source of market data. In that case an request reject may come back later on. If that happens, the listeners inherited onSubscriptionError method will be called, passing in the requestID supplied on this method.
        Specified by:
        addInstrumentDepthListener in interface IMarketDataStore
        Parameters:
        instrument - Instrument to listen to.
        listener - Object listening for updates.
        requestID - Optional identifier of this subscription request. May be null.
        Throws:
        SubscriptionException - if there was a problem making the subscription request to the underlying market data source.
